  You have an opportunity to make an unprecedented exploration of the  recently discovered star systems in the Andromeda Galaxy. Our astronomers  have plotted the stars which may have planetary systems and those star  coordinates can be provided. Since the Andromeda Galaxy is some 750,000  light years away, transit through a black hole will be required in order  for you to complete the journey within your lifetime.  The trip will be replete with dangers but with luck one can succeed.  No one knows what may be found in that far-distant galaxy but the rewards  could well be substantial. A singularity-enhanced hull with 190 cargo pods,  larger fuel tanks, and auto-repair is available to those who have bested  the rogue star, Maligna and recovered the Nemesian Star Gems. If you   qualify, your present hull can be replaced with this exceptional one.    CAUTION: Attempting this mission with a hull other than the Astraxial is             fool-hardy and the Space Authority will not be held responsible!